\section{INTRODUCTION}\label{INTRODUCTION}

\subsection{Scope}

This document gives the detailed design for the Print On Demand versions of the {\Product} user manuals.

\subsection{Purpose and Background}

To suggest an approach to publication by Print on Demand (POD) of the ProofPower user manuals.
To provide the detailed information required for submitting the manuals for publication.
To suggest minor changes to the manuals to make them more suitable for printing.

\subsection{Approach}

The proposed method for publication is as follows.

The manuals will be published through {\bf create}space, an Amazon company, and sold
through {\bf create}space and amazon web sites.
They may also be distributed through other {\bf create}space distribution channels for which they qualify.

Interior of the published books will be obtained by shrinking the PDF files for the relevant release
of {\Product} to the standard trim size of 8.5 by 11 inches, with the exception of the two reference
manals, which will need to be split into two volumes.
In the case of the reference manuals it is proposed that the second volume will be just the QWIC index
and that some minor changes be made to the manuals to provide a lightweight introduction to
the second volume.

I propose that all the USR documents be published in this manner, and that a new edition
of these be made for every major release of {\Product} with updates to the interior only for each
minor release.

We have the option to make these part of a series.

\begin{quote}
A series is a connected set of books. If this book is part of a series, identify where the book exists in the sequence with a volume number. We only accept volume numbers in numerical format ("1", "2", or "3"). Magazines and journals are also often grouped as a series. Identifying the series helps customers find other books in the series.
\end{quote}

I think that is probably a good idea.
The series would be ``ProofPower Manuals'' or ``ProofPower User Manuals'' (I'm not sure the ``User'' adds much).
It would be natural to use the document reference as the "number in series", extra references would be required
where manuals need to be split for printing.
Alternatively, the number in series need not have any significance.


\section{PROPOSED INTERIOR CHANGES}\label{PROPOSED INTERIOR CHANGES}

It is proposed that in the first instance the manuals be published with no changes,
and that any changes subsequently be implemented in the PDFs issued with ProofPower rather
than by creating a distinct set of PDFs for the printed manuals. except insofar as it may
prove necessary to resize the PDFs to fit the target trim ({\bf Create}Space will do this
automatically but the results are sometimes less satisfactory than prior print-to-file
using adobe acrobat).

The remainder of this section is concerned with alternatives, or with possible subsequent improvements.

Chapter 0 of the manuals might be reconsidered with a view to replacing them with
material more appropriate for a book.
One possibility would be to provide instead of chapter 0 a preface giving a brief
description of the book, together with appropriate aknowledgements.

The two reference manuals are at present too large to be published as single
volumes (the limit appears to be 630 pages for the proposed trim size).
The simplest way of achieving this is simply to chop off the keyword index
and put it in a second volume, without ceremony.
Perhaps some words of introduction might be placed at the beginning of the
section.
The first volume would still have an index, the cost of the second volume would
be very modest, and its separation would facilitate its use.

This works for the HOL and Z reference manuals insofar as the resulting page
counts are acceptable.
I don't know whether it is good for DAZ (is there a DAZ reference manual similar
to but bigger than the Z reference manual?).
In any case, we remain close to the limits, and so if the manuals were to
grow significantly another solution would have to be sought.
Perhaps putting the theory listings and related materials in a second volume,
with independeny indexes in the two volumes would be OK.

\section{THE SIGNATURE}\label{THE SIGNATURE}

The principal purpose of this document is to provide the information over and above
the interior PDF which must be submitted for publication of each volume, in a form
suitable for review in advance of publication.
These document will then facilitate the preparation new editions, permitting the
relevant online forms to be populated by reference to the DTD, using copy and paste
in many places.

